ccat:4010
	a	skos:Concept ;
	skos:broader	ccat:40 ;
	skos:closeMatch	wd:Q7498085 ;
	skos:definition	"The freight market consists of shipowners, charterers and brokers. They use four types of contractual arrangements: the voyage charter, the contract of affreightment, the time charter and the bareboat charter. Shipowners contract to carry cargo for an agreed price per tonne while the charter market hires out ships for a certain period. A charter is legally agreed upon in a charter-party in which the terms of the deal are clearly set out."@en ;
	skos:exactMatch	stw:13621-3 ;
	skos:inScheme	ccat: ;
	skos:notation	"4010" ;
	skos:prefLabel	"Freight"@en .

