ccat:4030
	a	skos:Concept ;
	skos:broader	ccat:40 ;
	skos:closeMatch	agrovoc:c_1b1e0e70 , eurovoc:434843 , stw:20762-1 , wd:Q8348417 ;
	skos:definition	"Permits and allowances in writing issued by a central authority (usually a governmental body) that allow a discharge of a specific quantity of a specific pollutant over a set time period. Polluters are required to hold permits in amount equal to their emissions. Polluters that want to increase their emissions must buy permits from others willing to sell them."@en ;
